cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the application of sparsity-exploiting algorithms to electron tomography, which involves image processing and signal processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of compressed sensing, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves numerical simulations, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses optimization parameters, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
